<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-35-0312 </DOCNO><TEXT>The parity of nuclear weapons between the United States and the SovietUnion has elevated the need and priority to continue our build-up andmaintenance of a strong conventional force to insure a viable deterrent.Since 1980, the Congress and the Defense establishment have recognizedour conventional military inferiority to the Soviets correlation of forces.There is, as the text of this paper substantiates, a critical shortfallin the balance and mix of our combat forces to implement and sustainour national defense and military strategy. One of the most significantstructural voids contributing to this imbalance is in the arm of cavalry.</TEXT></DOC>